blog.description: Brief Feminist Updates.  Feminism: Supporting the fight against the oppression of women through activism and the interrogation of the tools used to create and perpetuate a social system that oppresses women in order to afford privilege to men, especially white men. Tools like misogynistic narratives, ideas and attitudes and their use in politics, the media, education and all other social institutions and constructs. In addition, examining and pointing out how racism, homophobia and other oppressive systems and forms of discrimination intersect with misogynistic ideas creating hybrid attitudes, narratives and ideas against women of color, LGBT women, women with disabilities and other women who face those forms of discrimination.

body:
First Captain Marvel TV Spot Released

It might be Christmas Day, but Marvel Studios has given Captain Marvel fans present in the form of a new 30-second Captain Marvel TV spot.

There’s not really much new footage in this, it’s just edited differently, but with this 30 second spot ready it’s apparent that Marvel is getting ready to start promoting Captain Marvel in a big way leading up to March 8th.

This March, everything begins…

summary: What You Need to Know About Captain Marvel’s Cat | Nerdist
title: What You Need to Know About Captain Marvel’s Cat | Nerdist
excerpt: Every superhero movie should have a cat. Scratch that. Every movie should have a cat. Captain Marvel's meeting that all-important requirement by including Carol Danvers' adorable ginger feline companion, who was fully introduced in the latest trailer for the Marvel film after being teased in a poster. Nick Fury reacts as most people I know would to the kitty, cooing and calling it the cutest thing. He's right, of course, but Captain Marvel's cat isn't a cat at all. It's an alien known as a Flerken. What's a Flerken? You've probably already figured this out, but Flerken are alien creatures resembling Earth's house cats. You wouldn't notice any differences between the appearance of your best feline friend and a Flerken, and for the most part, they act exactly the same. Of course, physiological differences do exist. Flerken lay eggs to produce offspring (they can drop over one hundred at a time) and have tentacles that extend from their mouths. And they have human-level intellect. Still
